    <section id="about">
        <h2>About One Fair Justice</h2>
        <p>One Fair Justice was created from a simple belief: Justice should not depend on wealth, status, connections, or luck. It should depend only on truth, evidence, and fairness.</p>
        <p>Our mission is to restore trust through transparency, education, and civic engagement. We educate the public, highlight systemic problems, encourage constitutional literacy, and amplify stories where fairness intersects with justice.</p>
        <p>Long-term vision: Greater public awareness, informed policy discussions, and accessible legal education.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="research">
        <h2>Research & Articles</h2>
        <p>Investigative write-ups, legal explanations, and analysis on topics like judicial ethics, prosecutorial discretion, due process, and forensic science reliability.</p>
